task.summary:
Create the basic functions in algorithm and genotype
Created the wave function measurement for all individuals and added comments for TODO things. Created the initialization of parameters fo genotype and added the measure function for measuring the qRegister state. Questions arised about the measurement vector type. If a bool vector is used, it's harder to use this algorithm in existing problems. The solution is 'Binary' but it's storage method is weird and unintuitive. Further investigation is needed.

Add QuantumLookupTable, implement the QIGA, problems with Binary
Added the QuantumLookupTable class and an empty method. Implemented the QIGA adding necessary method calls and evaluations. Made QuantumRegister extend Binary and hold a vector<double> alphas_. When running the program it randomizes correctly (I guess) and finds awesome fitness results, but the calculated and found solution for function 1 don't add up.

Update the algorithm
The algorithm was reorganized to match the one from Wiki page. The register is also tweaked to suffice ECF's runtime workflow and replaced the alphas variable with thetas, adjusting with the initializer and measurment methods.
The quantum rotation gate still needs implementation.

Initialize the quantum rotation gate basics
Added the standard direction table and the adaptive rotation calculator.
Still need to calculate and implement the qRotation gate for register with thetas and resolve some issues with the look-up table.
